tipd: force ACE (CD321x) renegotiation for plugs present at probe

On Apple Silicon Macs, a USB3 device that is already plugged into a
USB-C port when Linux boots never link-trains: the xHCI port stays in
RxDetect forever because the CD321x ("ACE") PD controller firmware
negotiated the connection before the host PHY stack existed, and in
that state the external SuperSpeed path (which includes an on-board
retimer the host cannot reach in USB3 mode) does not present far-end
termination to the host. A physical replug always recovers, purely via
the generic hotplug path. macOS avoids this by renegotiating PD once
when its own ACE driver loads at OS handoff.

Fix: at the end of tps6598x_probe(), if a plug is already present on an
apple,cd321x port, issue the 4CC "GAID" command (controller cold reset)
and restore system power state S0. The ACE then renegotiates from
scratch and delivers a fresh PLUG_EVENT to the now-ready driver, and the
standard hotplug path (mux -> PHY -> dwc3 -> xHCI -> warm port reset ->
U0) brings the link up with no physical intervention.

Verified on Mac mini M1: 2x warm reboot + 1x cold boot, both ports,
both cable orientations.

Generated against kernel-16k 7.0.13-400.asahi (src.rpm source tree).
Applied with `patch -p1 --fuzz=0`; an application failure on a kernel
bump is intentional rot-check behavior — rebase this patch or drop it if
an equivalent fix has landed upstream.

--- a/drivers/usb/typec/tipd/core.c
+++ b/drivers/usb/typec/tipd/core.c
@@ -1860,6 +1860,33 @@
 	if (ret)
 		goto err_disconnect;
 
+	/*
+	 * Apple ACE (CD321x): a plug already present at probe time never
+	 * USB3-link-trains because the firmware negotiated the connection
+	 * before the host PHY existed; only a fresh negotiation makes the
+	 * external SuperSpeed path pass far-end termination. Cold-reset the
+	 * firmware (GAID) so the resulting PLUG_EVENT replays through the
+	 * normal hotplug path with the host stack ready.
+	 */
+	if (device_is_compatible(tps->dev, "apple,cd321x") &&
+	    (status & TPS_STATUS_PLUG_PRESENT)) {
+		int gaid_tries = 5;
+
+		dev_info(tps->dev, "plug present at probe; GAID reset to renegotiate\n");
+		ret = tps6598x_write_4cc(tps, TPS_REG_CMD1, "GAID");
+		if (ret)
+			dev_warn(tps->dev, "GAID write failed: %d\n", ret);
+		msleep(1000);
+		while (gaid_tries--) {
+			ret = tps->data->switch_power_state(tps, TPS_SYSTEM_POWER_STATE_S0);
+			if (!ret)
+				break;
+			msleep(200);
+		}
+		if (ret)
+			dev_warn(tps->dev, "S0 restore after GAID failed: %d\n", ret);
+	}
+
 	i2c_set_clientdata(client, tps);
 	fwnode_handle_put(fwnode);
 
